caption: The Chicken Patty was soo good.. I had the oxtails and rice.. also so good! I loved how our waiter Andres gave us recommendations on things to try. The vibes of the overall restaurant were soothing.. Can’t wait to go back..
Excellent food, experience and customer service by the entire staff. Great ambiance! Best to make reservations, wait time can be long at times.
Great spot for authentic Jamaican cuisine. The service was amazing and the ambiance was perfect.

First time dining at Yah Mon but will not be my last. Service was excellent.Very nice decor. I had Oxtails for the the first time. Very tender and delicious 😋 comes with red beans and rice, plantains. Also the Coco Bread is good. My husband had Lentil soup and Tofu Vegtables Curry with a Side Salad all very good.  Ocean Blue and Arnold Palmer cocktails good also. It's located next to Eagles cleaner on the very end.
The chefs do not cut any corners.  They put lots of thought into all the ingredients and details. Delicious!!!
Great

This will be a mixed review because the food was good. The issue I have is the pricing. I guess in a way, you are paying for the experience. You honestly can have better food at less than half the price at any other Caribbean restaurant. Because of the price, I had high hopes for the food. The Mac and cheese was not flavorful at all. I would not order that again but the Caribbean chicken platter was good. Very good quality chicken! The tables were very nice but man is it cold inside. Bring a jacket! There is also live music that can be a little loud and distracting sometimes. It's kind of cramped inside too. Overall it's a nice place that I will recommend. Just be prepared to spend some money cause it is expensive. I would go again but only if it was a special event.

I'm so full right now. The meal was so delicious that I didn't want to stop eating. The coco bread was warm and soft. The plantains were perfect. My brown stew chicken was so flavorful. I thought I was at a resort in Jamaica. We will definitely make this a favorite place in the downtown area. Andre and his wife are wonderful and work hard to bring us a nice dining experience.

Yah Mon hands down one of the best Caribbean restaurants!! For sure the best that I’ve had in Tampa. I’ve lived everywhere and even the Caribbean... The food and full experience dinning in Yah Mon will blow your mind while loving your soul and your body !!! Oxtails, jerked chicken.. man listen... check this place out !!

Yah Mon is outstanding!! It’s tucked away in a small plaza but a great find. I went with my sister, husband, brother in law, and parents. Everyone loved this truly authentic place. The jerk chicken, oxtail, and cauliflower bites were stand outs. Their cocktail menu is so fun too. The service was really excellent and the staff genuinely appreciates the business. I also got a little sauce on my white pants. When our sever noticed, he came back with a tide to go stain stick for me!! Please go here.

I made a reservation for my family and I got there and was turned away because apparently they did not put our name on list. I was embarrassed. Honestly they will never see me or any family members again
Excellent food and excellent service. Everything was cooked to perfection, the staff was so friendly. I’m here on business and I am so glad I found this restaurant. I strongly recommend Yah Mon
Excellent food, service and atmosphere. Look forward to dinning again

Just ordered from there this afternoon after my spouse put me on to them. Caribbean food is one of my favorites and have been hard pressed to find any good ones downtown. This place is a MUST go to.  The food was wonderful. As close to authentic as I’ve had in a very long time. The service was way better than I expected even when you compare the service to well known chains.  However, as a note, if you’ve never had Caribbean food before AND are not a fan of flavor (aka spices), this is not for you. The food had so much flavor and finally a place that can make really good jerk chicken.  Honestly hands down one of the most underrated places in the area. My sister is half Jamaican and she would certainly approve.

I would eat this 24/7 non stop for every meal possible!! Hands down the best Caribbean food in Tampa, amazing service and staff!! Plus locally owned and it has its own charm. Don’t even read the bad reviews there is nothing to complain about!!!!! Amazing food, service, people, and drinks! Hit up ya mon
Very friendly and helpful staff! Super delicious authentic food :)
Excellent customer service! Great covid protocols; temperature check and masks required. Great food a lot of options for vegan/vegetarian and fish lovers. 🤤🤗😋🥰
Great Customer service and vibes! Temperature check and masks at entry covid  protocol appropriate

Island food with island hospitality. I had the sampler was was my than filling. I think the oxtails is my favorite. The curry goat was on point too. I think the jerk chicken was too spicy 🌶 but others may enjoy it. I will be back for my samples.

The jerk chicken wings were excellent. They were tender and well-seasoned, very flavorful with enough spicy heat but not overwhelming the flavor of the rest of the seasonings. The Taste of the Islands was an ample serving of the basics from the menu, curry goat, chicken, oxtails (ordered extra), plantains,  and a spinach salad (for good measure), all very flavorful.  I was craving some good Caribbean food and Yah Mon definitely hit the spot.  Will be going back soon for dine- in.

Vegan Heaven! Best vegan curry I have ever had. I was astonished by the incredible flavor and the healthy, vibrant ingredients.  I found them on Happy Cow and after 8 years of having that app I had to finally make an account to leave an amazing review. Everyone would love this place. You could taste the good vibes in the food. I am so happy!! This food is medicine for the soul<3
The best Caribbean food and Amazing service!!!!
Definitely a must try if you're in the Tampa area ! Superb food , great vibes, and excellent customer service by the owner/servers!
Nice place for tasty caribbean food. Nothing but great experiences here. Bring your appetite because portions are large.

This place is a hidden GEM! It looks so unassuming on the outside but inside it's a luxurious dining establishment. And you haven't seen customer service this good since Chic-fil-a. This is a must for anyone who enjoys Jamaican food!
Food is delicious and the service is superb!
Amazing Food & the BEST service

Really home cooked and delicious take out oxtail. It was so full of depth of flavor. Super tender. Wow. The brown rice and plantains included were tasty too. Will return perhaps to try eating indoors.

Ordered the Whole Fish - as I have, many times before - for $24. Accustomed to receiving a roughly 1 pound Whole Red Snapper, w/ rice & a side salad, when ordering this dish from Nah Mon.  For some reason, this particular order arrived with a ½ - pound Whole Fish.  A Baby Snapper, if you will.  Charging the same price for half the amount of food is egregious. We literally could have fit two of the same-sized fish in the portion of the To-Go container allocated for the fish.  That's not okay. Neither is the inconsistency, relative to orders of the same dish we've placed in the past from this establishment.  Many of the other Jamaican, and West Indian, restaurants in the Tampa area can, at least, be counted on for their consistency. Unfortunately, We can no longer say the same about Nah Mon...
Amazing food and service! Highly recommend!!
Incredible food and very hospitable staff. 10/10

Excellent staff, service, and presentation. I must say the organic jerk chicken dish was fire,not bad at all. True,you are going to go deep down in your pocket $$. If you’re from the Caribbean,the prices will have you in shock😱 and you are going to find one thing or another to complain about. Yes, we all might know of or have our favorite hole in the wall spot but that is not what this place is.. Yuh in Hyde Park and just going by the name of the restaurant, you should know what you are in for.
Purchsed curbside to go for the first time and my wife and I are hooked! Flavorful and great portions...will be in for the entire experience soon!

I love Caribbean food and have experienced some of the best. This was right up there, in my top 5 hands down. There was something extra special about the seasonings used on the meats that stood out. The rice was supreme and their macaroni must be experienced. Im so glad they did not oversalt anything. Will return
Great place,a little on the pricey side but they have fairly large servings and the food and staff are great

Showed up late as they were closing and the owner personally kept the resturant open for us.  Ordered the oxtails and the island chicken platter.  Both were super delicious and the oxtails were flavorful and tender.  Wish I could go back and order more.  I highly recommend this place, especially for a date night.  Hands down the best Jamican resturants in Tampa.

Authentic Caribbean cuisine at its best in Tampa Florida. Ask for Andrea, he was our host and Waiter. He was sure to end or begin his statements with "Yah Mon" which I thought was brilliant considering that is the name of this establishment. He suggested the coco bread and curry dip sauce and jerk wings. Both were well tasting. For our entree we had both combination dishes. My wife had the oxtails, curry goat, jerk chicken, which came with rice&peas and a side salad. I had stew chicken, jerk chicken, oxtails, which also came with a side of rice&peas and a side salad. The food is plentiful, the atmosphere is relaxed and the service is above standard.  When next I am in town I will certainly be back for what this restaurant have to offer, great service and taste.  Best regards,  Brian

Found this place while searching for a place to go for mine and my husband's anniversary. We love spicy and Caribbean food. We were pleasantly surprised by how cute the restaurant was. Very romantic setting. Everyone there is as friendly as you can be and welcoming. I gathered that it is family run and even better because of that. We tried some appetizers, Caribbean Sampler and dessert and it was all 100% amazing! The flavors danced in our mouths. So much flavor and great seasonings. Our waiter was so nice and appreciative of us coming in. I couldn't have asked for a better dinner. It is our new favorite restaurant even though it is about 45 mins away. Well worth the drive.
Very professional, great customer service and great food. I will definitely be coming back here

Very disappointed in this place had high hopes based on the earlier reviews. For one I’ve had way better Caribbean food for cheaper price, oxtails were black not brown way too much browning I could taste it. Then the food wasn’t even enough for the price. Normally for what I spend in similar restaurants i be taking food home for the next day. Last but not least the drinks tasted like straight syrup i use to buy in Jamaica and mix with water. I definitely would not be going back and I wouldn’t recommend it. Better food waay cheaper at similar restaurants.

Foodie here, first let me say this, the place is nice and cute, good music and the waiter is very nice and a people person . . . However, I wasn’t impressed with my meal. The oxtails looked like TAR! Super black, salty and no type of anything to balance out the bitter and salty taste of the abundant amount of browning that was used (I would recommend some ketchup or brown sugar) also the amount of food isn’t enough for the price. I had a frozen drink and literally could not taste the alcohol . . . Tasted like an icee and had  to order an extra shot. I tasted the brown stewed snapper fish off my friends plate and I thought it was good.
Amazing food and very nice hosts! Love this place!
DELICIOUS pricey af But delicious. GREAT customer Service.
It Was good

Excellent service and delicious Caribbean food in an upscale setting.  There were many things I wanted to try on the menu, but the large servings made it hard to save room for dessert.  Will definitely be back!
Ox tails are really good they fall off the bone!

They have a wonderful ambiance. The service and hospitality of this restaurant exceeded my expectation. Very attentive very kind and helpful, they had great music at a low but audible level so it perfect! The food was delicious and I will definately be back soon 😊🥰

I don't know where to begin with how incredible this place is...so hang in there with me as I try my best.  We came in with a large group after coming from the beach. They did not seem to mind the messy hair, and flip flops. From the moment we walked in they treated us like we were royalty. The service received was even better than what we have received from a cruise ship. They bent over backwards to make sure we had everything we needed or wanted.  The food....THE FOOD!! So much flavor!!! WOW!!!! Not an exaggeration to say this was the best cornbread, salmon, chicken curry, brown stew, mac and cheese, pasta, and cornbread we have ever had!  We don't even live in Tampa but we will be back here just to come back to this restaurant!!!

Trying this place for the first time with a dine-out order and OM-YUM. Food packaging is on point. Food is delicious. This side salad is everything I didnt know I needed. I got the curry chicken, and my boyfriend had the ox tail. 100000000/10. Will definitely be back and bringing friends.
Food was amazing and the service was incredible
Great food- ordered take out, hit the spot. Can’t wait to sample more from the menu!

Everything was amazing! Literally as soon as you walk into the door till you left,it was an exceptional experience. Customer service,food, ambiance and everything else was amazing!
Lovely place for food and drinks!

We will definitely be back when we are in the area. Every penny we spent was truly worth it. God bless your establishment.

I'm new to the area and got home late one night, not feeling like cooking. Found this little gem down the road from my house. So, I thought I would grab something to carry home. Place was way nicer than I expected. Food was pretty good. If your craving Jamaican this is a good place to try.

The food and service were great. If you have never had a real Jamaican food this is the place to be and great atmosphere.

Highly over priced for unauthentic flavor. I ordered the brown stew chicken. I could taste some kind of spaghetti sauce in it. And the plantains served with it were tiny. And the salad on the side was two slices of cucumber garnished with tiny pieces of sweet peppers. Big disappointment.

I love this place I wish I found out about it years ago!! Do not hesitate to eat here! The vibes are there I promise great atmosphere, wonderful customer service from Andre’ !! And The BEST food I have had in a long time. Thank you I will be back!

Great ambiance, excellent food and service...
A preferred scene for delicious Caribbean food. Came in on a Weds. The service was very friendly and kind. The place has a cool feel to it.
Super delicious food and excellent service! Romantic vibe, perfect for date night!

The staff provided exceptional service from the phone call to make the reservations down to the departure. Me and my wife enjoyed the drinks and the flavorful food. The veggie burger was perfect! But, most importantly the service and presentation of the restaurant along with the food made our first visit one to remember.

Words can't describe how incredible this place is! I decided to have my girlfriends 30th birthday there. Andre mentioned they offer things to make the event extra special and boy did they deliver! From the decor, to the food, to the cake, to the champagne toast, to the music, I could not have asked for more. And to top it all off because the vibe was so spectacular I decided to make my girlfriend my fiancé that night at Yah Mon. If you have an event or just enjoy great authentic carribbean food Yah Mon is the place to be! We will definitely be back and thank you again to Andre his wife and the staff! You guys are the best!

Oh my goodness. Where do I begin? Beautiful decor, you won't see another Caribbean restaurant like it. Very clean and they took AMAZING precautions.  We had: Jerk Chicken Oxtails Curry Chicken Chicken & Beef Patties  Everything was beautifully cooked and incredibly delicious! The owners are sweethearts! I Will CERTAINLY be back!
Absolutely the best customer service ever! The food & drinks the fantastic. I will definitely be back! 🖤

I had an amazing time for my birthday with my girls. Owners were exceptional. Very hospitable and took care of us. The food was amazing and great portions. Definitely will be back and tell my friends.
Amazing customer service and food!
Food and service is AMAZING! The food is delicious and authentic. The atmosphere is elegant relaxing and the waiter is great and attentive. HIGHLY recommend and will definitely be back!!!!!
The place was simply exceptional; in a class by itself. I highly recommend this spot. Very romantic

This was my 3rd visit to the restaurant and each experience was nothing but EXCELLENT! The owner Andre served us and was extremely pleasant and patient with my many request! One of the worst Jamaican restaurant i have ever been. They don't even carry scotch bonnet pepper. Even the corner store food place in Fort Lauderdale carries it smh.
We chose this place based on the reviews. Honestly, we were disappointed. I believe they want to provide a great experience, but it was lacking in my opinion. The food was mediocre for the price.
Great food! Awesome customer service!

On summer vacation from Pittsburgh pa. We where liking for so jerk and curry chicken and this place IS IT!!!! Everything was soooo good! The best curry chicken I be had and my husband loved the jerk chicken. 1st time having coco bread and it was soft and sweet. Honey bbq wings where very good as well.
I love Jamaican food and the oxtails and jerk chicken are delicious. I’m a Caribbean woman so I appreciate authenticity in my food. Eat & be happy!!

My favorite Mexican restaurant in St Pete. I was a manager years ago at a made from scratch fresh Mexican restaurant. I would definitely dine here again and I encourage others to do the same!
Where do I begin? Amazing food, awesome service, terrific ambiance.. loved my experience, and I can assure you that I'll be back soon! Thank you for the wonderful dining experience!

I stopped in for a nice dinner for a friends birthday. I had the jerk wings and cornbread and it was really tasty. The spice had so much flavor but the food wasn’t even the best part. The staff there was so welcoming and kind. The manager and server were excellent and very friendly.
Just went here for the first time with a friend tonight. Exceptional service from start to end. Great music and fantastic food. I’ll bring many friends back. Thank you to Andre for a great night!

The service was excellen, nice friendly and promt, and the food omgggg, it was excellent!!!!! I will be back again, and I recommend anyone who is looking for a good meal and nice environment to pay then a visit, you wont regret it!!!!!

This place is amazing.  We were introduced to this restaurant by some friends and can not wait to to back.  The food was excellent and the service top notch.  I immediately forwarded their information to my friends who like to take their wives somewhere nice to eat.  It's a must try in my book.  Do I love this place? YAH MON!!

AMAZING!  Some of the best Caribbean food I've had. Everything was perfectly seasoned and delicious. The oxtail was out of this world.  Entire family loved every every dish. Service is also outstanding. André made us feel very welcome, as if we had been invited to his home.  Will definitely come back here again!!
Amazing food, amazing service, great interior setting.

Wow, what an experience. The food was cooked to perfection with unique spices at the right time. The service was one of a kind- best in the bay so far. One of the most elegant, unique touches of Caribbean food you will not forget. Their food was authentic, organic and taste like it was straight from the islands.
Great flavor! The Goat curry was fall off the bone delicious. I'll be back 👐

Wow, where to begin!! We absolutely not just love the food but the first class service!! The owners are fantastic, and it gives us great joy and pride to support Yah Mon.  No cons....all positive!!  We just moved here to Tampa  (Military) and wanted some good Jamaican food and we found our “place to go”!  1st of all we were amazed that they had everything on the menu ready to order (which is rare) We truly tried to order everything off the menu lol.....and nothing disappointed us!  The flavors and quality were spot on!!!  The oxtails were tender the rice and peas were flavorful they even had homemade sorrell (delicious drink) And the stew chicken was incredible!! We washed it down with sweet tea and bread pudding and mango key lime pie!! Please go! I highly recommend Yah Mon.

Very good food here. Much tastier than your typical restaurant. The staff was friendly and attentive, and given the situation they also brought out wipes to clean your hands. I sampled a variety and I definitely am a fan of the jerk wings, jerk chicken, and goat. Hope to be back again!

Nice atmosphere. Very nicely decorated. The food was very authentic and so delicious.This placed wowed me in every way! The jerk wings were very good the right amount of spice too! Awesome place!!!!The red snapper was just omg.soyummy. This place deserves a Michelin star. A+ = YAHMON!

Yah Mon is the best Caribbean food restaurant.I hope to come back to Yah Mon.I had the most amazing experience here,there was awesome service too. The food was perfectly seasoned and it was delicious.They have many options for vegans too.This place is way better than I expected.They also had perfectly priced food I was really surprised on how a wonderful evening we had at YAH MON.... call your friends and family and go hang out.

Yah Mon is the best Caribbean restaurant in all of Tampa, FL. Yah mon makes well cooked food! The service is amazing too! I had oxtails and it was out of this world.It was the best Caribbean food I have ever tasted!This is the most amazing restaurant in general. I had the best experience!!!

YESSIRRRR THIS CHICKEN BE SO GOOD I RECOMMEND EVERYONE GO TO THIS RESTURANT RIGHT NOW I PROMISE U U WILL NEVER HAVE ANY OTHER FOOD LIKE THIS FOOD 🤤 🍗
Hands down the best service and wings.  Be careful they have a kick to them.  The wings not the service.
He was AMAZING! Food AMAZING! The experience with the owner/ manager was awesome! Please try this place.
I’ve been here twice and have not been disappointed yet. The setting is a lil romantic and they play good reggae music. i got the curry chicken dish it also comes with plantains, It was DE-LI-CIOUS.

Id give 0 stars if i could . Unfortunately these people put up a front that they are self mad christian people yet they dont pay their workers .. VERY MUCH WAGE THEFT at its finest . Hasn’t happened to 1 worker but a handful !!

Went here the week we were looking at schools for daughter. This is a hidden gem and the food was superb and refreshing. The staff was beyond professional and attended to everything, even explaining the dishes we were served. If you are passing by or just live in the area I think you should try it out. Not far from casino, great food and the place is just lovely inside. The bread serve with butter is dresmy. Very very very GOOD!!!!!😋

Had a great meal here tonight even though it wasn’t exactly what I ordered! My wife and I came here with our aunts and two daughters for dinner. My daughter had eaten before we arrived and promised to be good as Long as she got ice cream. So when the waiter came I ordered all of the food and a cup of ice cream for my daughter. I ordered the taste of the islands which was supposed to be a plate of curry goat, Some oxtail and jerk chicken. Before our food arrived we had to ask multiple people for the ice cream which eventually came after our drinks and appetizers. When the food arrived we realized that I had gotten the wrong dish. It was a sampler of different carribean meat dishes, but they were all chicken. either way the food tasted good and my daughter ended up getting the ice cream eventually. I was still charged for the more expensive meat dish but it was only about 4 dollars more expensive so I didn’t complain. My aunts ordered the snapper which tasted amazing as well but they had to dig around all the bones, of which there were plenty. All in all great flavor but there was room for improvement.

Absolutely, hands down a great restaurant with phenomenal tasting food!!!  The ambience and customer service was amazing. Must visit and I definitely will be coming back whenever I am visiting Tampa!!!

Great family owned restaurant, the owner is very personable and makes sure each dining experience is amazing. The food was absolutely worth the wait, for a small space the ambience is still great, and the portions were perfect. I absolutely devoured the oxtails, loved the setting and can’t wait to come back. Yah Mon!!!!!
Man this place blew me away! 5 stars is for real! Great Meal! These ppl will put their heart and soul into your meal!
I met my brothers in the Lord for dinner and a meeting. Andre was introduced to us and he made us feel Welcomed. The meals were just as if we had gone to visit family t eat. Very enjoyable.
Great service, great food, great atmosphere.

Went here in March 2020 in a party of 6 people for a family event. Service was top notch, clean and friendly atmosphere. Individual portion sizes are huge  (I had the "Taste of the Islands"). I highly recommend this establishment and cannot wait until my next visit!

Great dinner and service, large portions. This is an add on to my prior review several months ago. Ate there again and the prices have gone up quite a bit.prices on this site are wrong. Food still very good .
Quality West Indian food. Bring your appetite! I will be returning the next time I am in town.
The food was ok but overpriced. It's not authentic Caribbean. The flavor was on the food, not in the food. Try the wings👍🏿
Very Friendly Staff, Clean, Authentic Food.
Food was amazing, service was top notch.  Will definitely be going back.
Beautiful restaurant with great food tucked in the corner. Ordered one of their platters and everything was delicious! Looking forward to going back soon. This is definitely a date night spot.

First of all, I have nothing but genuine praise for this restaurant! In fact, we were so pleased with everything that we said a little prayer that they stay in business for a long time and get the chance to expand!!! Now, we chose it from a selection of places for my girlfriend’s bachelorette dinner especially after seeing the decor of the place! It’s a beautiful black owned restaurant with amazing service! The owners who are husband and wife were so kind and made us feel welcomed and at home. The ambience was perfect for a nice classy dinner with friends or a romantic dinner for two. Secondly, the food - Oh MY Gash!!! The jerk chicken, ox tails and curry chicken were delicious and seasoned to perfection. Note; if you like spicy jerk, this is is the place to be. True to the word of the owner, the meat fell off the bones! The specially made shots were delicious and tropical! Though it may seem pricey at first, I promise that it is worth it!! I think for me, the service was the best part of this experience! They were efficient and timely and everyone  was so polite! Janise and Andre are superb! This place is a must whenever you’re in Tampa!
This place was amazing m. Beautiful ambiance and the food was amazing. The owners were very kind and attentive. Curry chicken was so seasoned!
The food was great but the service was slow.
This place was is wonderful! So welcoming and the food was fantastic. Will return next time we are in the area.
GREAT FOOD. GREAT SERVICE. OVERALL AN AMAZING EXPERIENCE, and the staff make you feel right at home.
Best restaurant in tampa great service and great food you must eat here an awesome experience kayla is the best server she will put a smile on your face.
The service is second to none. Authentic Caribbean food. Dark and stormys are really great!

I am a good Trini cook myself...and I was impressed by this place. I had the Taste of the Caribbean entree. Everything was flavorful  and delicate. The ambience was warm and cozy and the service was impeccable. The experiences left me saying " Yah Mon!"

Absolutely love the food here and the atmosphere first went at gasparilla two years ago and they were short on servers but the owners are so kind and hospitable I didn’t even care still recommending them to this day

Testy food are here but price is so high.

Being from Chicago - it was great to try something different here in Tampa. The wait staff genuinely tries to strike a conversation and remembers your name after they ask which is not something you see everywhere anymore!

Had dinner tonight. The food was delicious and the inside is way more elegant than any Caribbean spot I’ve ever been to. I’m a bathroom snob, and even that was very clean and nice. Alexis and Andre waited on us and they’re customer service was impeccable. We’ll definitely be back a few more times.
Not sure. Didn't get the chance to eat here because it was closed. We came on a Tuesday after MLK day and google said it was opened until 10pm and it wasnt. :(
AMAZING food!! Big portions and great service! So glad to have found this gem and enjoy the wonderful food!! Would gladly return if I am ever back in Tampa! Keep up the great service and work!
Had the platter. Jerk chicken was awesome, the oxtail & goat curry were ok. Rice was meh!
I love this restaurant! Uniquely delicious! Economical, as well!
The salmon and wings were really good. I went with a friend for a birthday lunch. I will be back . thanks
This place is amazing for breakfast!! And reasonably priced!! The staff was awesome! We enjoyed our drinks and food.
So good! Great staff! Amazing food!

This placed wowed me in every way! I took my mom here tonight for dinner, it was a very special birthday dinner! The first thing we had was a sort of pastry with a warm sweet cheese filling and I knew I was in for something amazing.. my mom ordered the chicken trio and I ordered the curried vegetables. Before I even had a bite the aroma won the 5 stars! I mean this meal had me taking breaks so it wasn't over too soon haha. Seriously you need to hit this spot. The recipes are from the Cook's grandmother, truly a family joint with class, style, service and deliciousness!

On New Years Eve with a reservation for 8:45, we waited to be seated. Then waited for our order to be taken, waited to eat, waited, and waited. An hour passed before we received any food, the waitresses asked 4 separate times what soup we ordered, and after all the waiting the food was just okay. The one waitress was really nice though. The whole restaurant was full of people on different ends of the waiting spectrum. Sevral people ended up leaving. Wouldn't recommend for a holiday visit!
Loved the atmosphere, the service, and the food. Thank you for the amazing ! Yah Mon!
Nice atmosphere. Very nicely decorated. The food was very authentic and so delicious. The workers gave us their undivided attention. Awesome experience.

It was a pleasure having dinner at this awesome restaurant! Customer service was unquestionably the BEST , the food was great! We will certainly visit again soon. Thank you Andre and staff for your awesome hospitality and certainly for making us feel welcome. The drinks were delicious too.
Fantastic area with great food. The employees are always friendly. Highly recommended.
This place is the real deal. Jerk chicken was what I got and it’s excellent but it is spicy. Nice local business and good service. A must try if you’re stopping by!

I come to this excellent place from time to time since I like the good mood that is exist in this place. The team is awfuly helpful and qualified. The service is absolutely quick. Needless to say, the food they serve is magnificent. I frequent often and I was always joyful. The cost is reasobable. I recommend this place to to all.

There is zero question as to why this place is rated a solid 5 stars out of so many reviews. From the moment we walked in we were greeted by what has to be the single most professional and thorough server I have ever encountered. The man (Andre) shook my hand as I entered the door. Things like that are too often overlooked and forgotten in today's day and age. Everything, including the adult beverage I had, was stellar. The chef is a freaking rockstar. A true artist. Nothing left the kitchen that wasnt 5 stars worthy. Amazing experience. They even had dedicated tables for date nights and anniversaries. Keep up the great work!

I'm so glad I gave this restaurant a try! Had the Taste of the Islands platter. Everything was great, but the curry goat was phenomenal. The service and kindness from everyone on staff was much appreciated. If I lived in Tampa, I'd come here regularly. If you've had authentic Caribbean food either back in the islands or somewhere like NYC, you won't be disappointed coming here!
Great food, great service, classy and friendly vibe. Definitely coming back!
Good food at great prices. Services was great.

I took a friend to Yah mon to celebrate her birthday. Andrea and Janise have a wonderful restaurant establishment. Atmosphere is nice and the food is tasty. I agree with others reviews, prices is a tad bit high. My personal opinion all meals should come with veggies. Drinks should be more clearly described of the rum infused mixture. However I would go again.
All we can say is YAH MON! The service is impeccable and the food is amazing! If you like Caribbean style food, look no further than this gem of Tampa!
Nice ambiance, good food and friendly service.
Yah Mon is the best Caribbean restaurant in the Bay area,  hands down

Went with my wife on a date night and the food is amazing. Very deep, rich flavors, cooked with love and attention to detail. This is an upscale restaurant, so don’t come here complaining about price like some like reviewers. But it is absolutely worth the price. Service is also phenomenal very down to earth people who take a lot of pride in what they do. I would recommend this spot to anybody. AAA food and service.

This restaurant  was awesome, I highly  recommend  it if you have a taste of the Caribbean.  If you have  ever been to the Caribbean and experienced that A1 customer service, you will definitely receive it here. Andre had me so excited about how awesome the food was, I was  trying everything. The red snapper, with brown gravy and stewed was awesome and I highly recommend it. Plantains, coconut water, a new dish made with cauliflower was great, macaroni and cheese great. Again this is a definitely  go to restaurant for you Caribbean palette.  Lastly,  the ambiance was perfect, music, high back white booths set the mood.  I will definitely  be back with friends.

The sheer aroma led me here. I was walking to another restaurant but stopped here instead just by the smell and ambience. I went on a friday around 830. It was such a candlelit mood, but there is space for a bar to watch the game if you so please. Reservations could certainly help because shortly after I arrived as a party of one more patrons arrived and the small venue filled quickly. There was a bit of a wait, but their menu online and most importantly their host informed me that they were running behind and that they would be euth me shortly. They also cook their food fresh with organic ingredients. You could tell the difference immediately. Once my food arrived I wasnt concerned with the wait. The jerk chicken was so tender and juicy I could slice through it with a fork. The curry goat was savory and the oxtail was tasty. I enjoyed their selection of beverages that ranged from organic kombucha and water to hot tea or soda. I should have taken pictures. I would recommend. Just be aware of the initial wait time....abt 15 minutes depending on when you arrive and staffing.
ya mon good place
Different experience and tasty vegan food

The place was amazingly clean,  the staff were very kind and willing to compromise. Although they are slightly pricey, it is very worth the delicious food, relaxing environment, and courteous staff.  They also have student discounts.
Great atmosphere and service. Brown Stew Red Snapper was delicious!

Visited Yah Mon with some colleagues while visiting Tampa. The venue was awesome; small yet very elegant, presentable and comfortable. The food was very tasteful; a mix of a the Caribbean. The customer service was stellar; staff engaged with us from arrival to departure. We tried several options from the menu (oxtail, curry, jerk, stew). Flavors were a complementary blend to represent the diversity of the islands. Food, texture, seasoning was well prepared. Clean reggae, and various genres of music to set the tone. Highly recommended to all; looking for a taste of the islands, relaxed atmosphere and just good vibes. Impressed!

Cute black and white decor, romantic look nice music.  Over priced food, 1 drink cost $14.99 one drink!!  I was shook. Not elegant enough for those prices it's a store front restaurant and if it's that much for one drink put it on the menu. But great place other other wise

Had dinner with my wife. She had the brown stew chicken and I had the brown stew snapper. The food was amazing and the service even better. Prices are reasonable and the portions are large. I recommend putting this restaurant in your monthly rotation.
Great atmosphere, staff were courteous and respectful. Food was good but a "LIKKEL" pricey but a good spot for a date or family evening.
Amazing food, even better people! Andre and the team could not be better. Oxtail for the sweet and tender, jerk chicken for the heat. So happy we stopped. We'll be back.
The food was amazing!  The staff was second to none with their service.  I wish I could eat here every week.
A hidden gem. Intimate. White table. Delicious dishes. Charming staff. Restrooms tastefully decorated, classy, and high tech efficiency

Me and my boyfriend decided to call in and order some food.. We went in to wait and got a drink or 2 and ended up eating there because of the great vibe we caught with the staff..  The food was sooo good and made me feel like I was in the islands !!  I got the oxtails that were falling off of the bone and my boyfriend got the taste of Islands(I think), he had oxtails, curry goat and jerk chicken .. Everything was tasty..  Customer service was bomb too!!  Made me feel like I was at home :-)

Ya Mon was FAB U LOUS!!!! The venue was beautiful, the service was impressive and the food was impeccable!! The owner Andre and his wife are doing a great job in this space! I had the Jerk wings (great), plantains (tasty) and the ox tails with salad and peas and rice (outstanding). This is a MUST VISIT in Tampa!

My colleagues and I visited the restaurant and were amazed by the food and the service. The staff was extremely professional and keep the restaurant impeccable. They even wear gloves to keep everything clean. The food was HEAVENLY!! Everything is very fresh. I had salmon with a sweet potato and side salad. For a starter we ordered roti and coconut bread. For dessert I had rum cake. The food portions were very satisfying. The restaurant itself is very clean looking with white table clothes, white booths. But it also has a cozy feeling with floral arrangements and affirmations written in wood on the tables. I HIGHLY recommend this restaurant!!
Delicious
This place was amazing. Services was great. Food was good. Everything was well maintained. Great atmosphere.
Delicious food with excellent service in a lovely environment.  We enjoyed the curry and brown chiicken stew.

Awesome service.  Very friendly staff.  Coco pan was unremarkable and should have been free, tasteless. Red Snapper was perfect along with the bread pudding.  Used the sauce from the red snapper to flavor the beans and rice (also somewhat tasteless).  Good for a date night, but don't order the coco pan.
Excellent all around. The decor is beautiful. The service is outstanding and the food is delicious. We will definitely be coming again even though it is an hour trip

Don't let the outside fool you, this place is a gem!! First off, the interior is beautiful! Intimate booths & comfy bar seats. The food is delicious & tastes very authentic! Hubby & I ordered the taste of the islands (3 dishes in 1) & the waitress even suggested a sequence of tasting to allow the heat to build, she was right! Cannot say enough nice things about the staff, everyone was very professional & attentive. We came on a busy Saturday night & even though they were slammed service did not falter. A must visit in Tampa! 😎👍🍹

The food was delicious and service exceptional! I had the Tast of the Islands meal. The oxtail was so rich and decadent. The goat curry was phenomenal. The jerk chicken was moist and flavorful. The staff were very attentive. I'll be back the next time I'm in the area.
Excellent service and some intense jerk!

I think the real star  is the service you get at Yah Mon, the owner came by our table and asked us what we thought and you could tell he genuinely wanted to know and had so much pride in the fact that his wife cooked all the dishes!If you haven't been to this local Caribbean restaurant I highly recommend it....and don't let the exterior scare you, it's modest and located next door to a Walgreens, but inside is just beautiful.
Our first time at this classy restaurant and we loved the experience, we will deff be back. Excellent food, friendly people, and great atmosphere ❤️

What a gem! If you love Caribbean food or are intrigued by it, check this place out! From the graciousness of the host, to the fantastic staff, and the unbelievably awesome food, this place is just fantastic! The food is delicious and the portions are gigantic. The drinks which are made with wine-based alcohol instead of the traditional spirits were great. Great dining experience. Thank you Yah Mon.
Great meal. Will be back soon.
Food and ambiance were great as well as the service.

Fist time going to Yah Mon and it was EXCELLENT! Great Food. Magnificent Service! Authentic Caribbean dishes that taste just like the Islands. Tampa’s hidden jewel! What a nice place to eat. Not often you find a Caribbean restaurant that is not a hole in the wall place but this is very nice. I sat at the bar and chatted with the owners who are great hosts. My jerk chicken was nice but it was hot. If you have sinus problems you will be cured. I will definitely be back.

This is the absolute best experience you will have at any restaurant in the Tampa area. Phenomenal staff, lovely decor and above all else...AMAZING CARIBBEAN FOOD!! We tasted a little bit of everything and were pleased with every bite. From the patties to the oxtails or curry goat, you will be in for a treat. The bread pudding and rum raisin ice cream will blow you away. I simply cannot say enough about this gem of a restaurant. Our server was Alexis and she was superb. Very attentive and pleasant. Yah Mon will not disappoint.
What a fantastic restaurant. The inside is just gorgeous. The staff is so friendly and accommodating. Andddddd the food is awesome!!!
Amazing food my first time having Caribbean cuisine and I loved every second of it atmosphere was amazing and the service was great!!!
Amazing Caribbean food.
Incredible food and service. One of the best dining experiences I have had in Tampa Bay. I would highly recommend stopping by!

I went to this place because of the reviews. Very high rating. That being said I did not have that experience. Yes the decor is nice and the food was good but way over priced! Although our server forgot everything under the sun and only came to our table twice, the other servers helped out after we got their attention. Overall just an okay experience.
Curry Chicken was so good !!! THank you for amazing service YAH MON!

had an amazing time took my girlfriend here and she loved the food jerk chicken was out of this world! great staff even better food!

Been here twice with my fiancé, we enjoyed this place very much! We have been consistently impressed by the quality of the service, the main guy there seems to run a tight ship, although some of the servers could use a bit more experience. The jerk and stew chicken is great too, portions are generous. It’s not a cheap place but it is in the heart of south Tampa so.... we all know how that goes. Fresh coconuts are a big win in my book, and atmosphere is very pleasant. Will be back!

Been here twice with my fiancee, we enjoyed this place more than other local Caribbean restaurants because of the authenticity of the food! There is one chef who prepares every plate in the house. Having spent years in the service industry I'd like to give "big ups" to the chef for pushing out such impressive volume and maintaining the quality of each and every plate and the staff for staying cool and calm during a push.  They treat you like family. We have tried the chicken platter, oxtails, jerk and curry chicken, and their stew chicken is really incredible. Great atmosphere, well decorated. They serve full natural coconuts too so that's awesome! Theres no liquor license here so dont expect drinks to kick your butt but they are delicious and fun recipies. They do need a better POS solution though as check processing can take a while due to lack of machines.

Amazing food and drinks all around. But absolutely MUST try the amazing jerk wings. Fall off the bone tender wings. I've almost tried everything on the menu and I love everything. Especially the oxtail.

Incredible food! Certainly food I would never be able to produce in the privacy of my own home! Curries, the chicken stew, ox tail and jerk chicken soooo good. Service excellent. I can't wait to go back!

Just had an incredible dining experience in Tampa. After years of traveling the Caribbean I have finally found a place that captures all the tastes and smells of the best of the regions foods. Ox tail. Jerk chicken. Goat. Amazing flavors!!!! The most attentive staff in a long time. Let Andre and his crew WOW. YOU!!!
Caribbean food and service at this place is excellent. Dropped in on Mon I think. The staff was very kind and attentive. Prices are reasonable I would say.

We had a really great time celebrating my dear friends birthday.  Andre was our waiter and he was a class act. Everyone annihilated their food. The whole ambiance is great and the encouraging words love, faith, and others through out make a huge difference.
Staff very attentive. Excellent food and we will be back. Jah bless
Great food, decor, music, & service.

This along with the food tasting out of this world caused me to leave a 35% tip😄. Worth every penny we and then some.

Amazing food and atmosphere! The service was awesome! Best Caribbean Restaurant in the Tampa Bay Area! I had the jerk chicken, curry chicken, rice and peas & the virgin sunset island drink all I can say is ...YAH MON!

The best restaurant I’ve ever been to! So elegant and wonderful environment! Great staff, Food, drinks, dessert, and music! Just an experience you have to have! I would choose Yah Mon to celebrate every occasion I have over and over!

Crazy good food, crazy great people and a wonderful dining experience. Props too for the table side credit card payment process. Love this place and though it takes a little effort to find it, Yah Mon is absolutely worth the trip for Caribbean dishes.
Went in.....it was wayyyyy to expensive for the experience!!
Fantastic restaurant where you least expect it!! Everything was a pleasure frok the food to the service, the history and decor. Definitely going to have to come back!.

Great environment. Food is Awesome!!! Met one of the owners and she was so polite and gracious.  Gave me some extras for being a first time customer.  :)
Excellent food and good service! The employees were super nice and and the food tasted wonderful. I will most definitely  come back and tell others !

Excellent place to eat and relax, this has to got to be the best place in Tampa for Caribbean food thus far Welcoming atmosphere and great people. You at home once you enter Loved it.....

Yah Mon is a jewel in the Tampa restaurant crown.  If you are a lpver of Jamaican cuisine you are sure to find a familiar favorite dish here presented in a notably upscale manner.  If you are new to the island's food offerings then there is no better place to introduce your palate to it.  This establishment is family run with an obvious sense of pride and attention to detail.  The ambiance is fancy yet unpretentious.  Every face is friendly and accomodating.  I have not encountered another Jamaica. Restaurant in Tampa that is a true memorable "date night" spot. Yah Mon is unquestionably a place to have that first date to impress or to celebrate a special night with a special person.
Food was good.  I liked the Ox tails
Never been here before, glad i came. The food and atmosphere was awesome!

Tasty but not great service.

Had an amazing date here. Tia was our server and she was fabulous, as well as Andre, the manager! The food was awesome. I had the Jerk Chicken and it was spiced perfectly. The patties were good... I actually preferred the vegetable over the beef. And the bread pudding was very tasty, especially with the rum ice cream. All in all, we will definitely be back!

Walked here with my wife and toddler son from our hotel (he hitched a ride in our baby carrier).  Upon entering, I was taken aback by the decor, it was new, super clean, modern, and had TV's playing all kinds of sports (Rugby, Cricket, Basketball, etc).  I immediately thought 'There is no way they have a high chair'... Well after we were immediately greeted and seated (by who I later found out were the owners) they brought out the best high chair I have seen at a restaurant!  It matched the decor, had adjustable straps, and a removable tray/top.  We ordered drinks (both great) and chips with mango salsa.  When the salsa arrived they also brought out apples and grapes in an Elmo cup for our son!  I watched them bring out something similar for another couple with a kid. The entree's we ordered were fantastic (I have never had fall off the bone tender chicken that was this good before!... and in three different flavors!), plenty of food, too much in fact that I didn't finish or leave room for dessert.  I can't recommend this place enough, sincere staff/owners, fantastic decor, super clean, great for couples, and family's with small children, and downright amazing food.

First time in Tampa Fl and Yah Mon is a fantastic place to dine. I ordered the chicken platter and it was delicious.. The chicken was tender.. If you like a little spice the Jerk chicken was on point! The brown stewed chicken was my favorite! The curry chicken was so good . If you are ever in Tampa FL please show Andre and his wife support and love! Customer service, atmosphere, and food fantastic.. ♥️♥️

The food is DELICIOUS! The staff is very friendly.  The wait time is a bit long but the end results are definitely worth it! I had the "Taste of the Islands. If I'm ever in Tampa FL.again I will be returning to Yah Mon!
Had an amazing time at Yah Mon. The food was great as well as the staff! I  highly recommend this place if you are ever in Tampa!
First time here and the food was amazing. Great atmosphere. Will definitely come here again.

This is the best restaurant in Tampa if not all of Florida. Great ambience and great welcoming staff. The food is on another level.

When another server noticed me low on a drink she stopped to ask. Very cool!  As for the food, unique and delicious!  My wife had the brown stewed chicken, to die for!  There were some potatoes spread sparingly throughout the stew and oh ma goodness!  Good stuff!  I had the oxtail/jerk chicken/curry goat entree and every bit of it was excellent. No problems munching that stuff right along with the meat attached!  It’s that good!  As for the jerk chicken...  yup, it hot.  Not irritatingly hot, just a good kick in the tongue. If you don’t like heat, I would share this with someone else. As for me, loved it. Hard to explain it. Not juicy but not dry. It’s just jerk chicken. Exactly the way it’s supposed to be IMO.  One last thing to say about the place, it is well managed. Not sure if our server may have been part of the ownership or not, but he was very professional. There was a slight hiccup in our order, an appetizer simply failed to come out but he noticed the mistake, turned it right on its head and brought it out with dinner free of charge. This is just the restaurant guy in me coming out but I do have to applaud the commitment to customer experience. No empty apology, no excuse. Although we declined politely, (and we didn’t mind a bit, really!) he insisted. Bravo folks!  A simple one on a million mistake turned into something that makes a happy customer brag on you!  That’s it for anyone wanting a review, as for the end of my little thing here, I just wanted to say hats off to the Yah Mon staff. My wife and I thoroughly enjoyed our evening and talked about how much we loved it all the way home. You all deserve a quick mention, not from google but right from the Sloan family. We wish you continued success and will visit each and every tine we are in Tampa. We’ll be relaying our experience to our family and friends!  Thank you for a wonderful meal!
